    • Field Detail

      • state

        WebSocketMessageState state
        Indicator of the current completeness of a given WebSocketMessage instance.

      • rawMessage

        private Binary rawMessage
        The raw binary of a given instance of WebSocketMessage. Initially empty, but appended to as the provider WebSocketListener calls process(Binary).

      • NOT_SET

        public static final int NOT_SET
        Assigned to numeric variables before they have been set.

        This allows for an easy (and uniform) way to check if a certain numeric field in a WebSocketMessage has been set yet, as there is no way for a numeric field to be set to a negative value otherwise.

        See Also:
        headerSize, payloadLengthBytes, payloadLengthPlaceholder, Constant Field Values

      • PLS_SMALL

        public static final int PLS_SMALL
        Constant used to denote the smallest number of bits that can precede either the maskingKey, or the payload, depending on whether or not the masked boolean is true. Set to 16b/2B.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PLS_MEDIUM

        public static final int PLS_MEDIUM
        Constant used to denote the middle-sized number of bits that can precede either the maskingKey, or the payload, depending on whether or not the masked boolean is true. Set to 32b/4B.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PLS_LARGE

        public static final int PLS_LARGE
        Constant used to denote the largest number of bits that can precede either the maskingKey, or the payload, depending on whether or not the masked boolean is true. Set to 80b/10B.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
